    • Method Detail

      • dealPlayer

        void dealPlayer​(Player player,
                int delay)
         throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Deal cards to the player as follows
 
 1. deal a card to the player
 2. call GameEngineCallback.nextCard(Player, PlayingCard , GameEngine)
 3. continue looping until the player busts (default value of GameEngine.BUST_TOTAL=42)
 4. call GameEngineCallback.bustCard(Player, PlayingCard, GameEngine)
 5. call GameEngineCallback.result(Player, int, GameEngine)
    with final result for player (the pre bust total) 
 6. update the player with final result so it can be retrieved later
        Parameters:
        player - the current player who will have their result set at the end of the hand
        delay - the delay between cards being dealt (in milliseconds (ms))
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - thrown when delay param is < 0 or > 1000

      • dealHouse

        void dealHouse​(int delay)
        throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Same as dealPlayer() other than the two notes below but deals for the house and calls the
 house versions of the callback methods on GameEngineCallback, no player parameter is required. 
 
 IMPORTANT NOTE 1: At the end of the round but before calling calling GameEngineCallback.houseResult(int, GameEngine) 
 this method should iterate all players and call applyWinLoss(Player, int) 
 to update each player's points
 
 IMPORTANT NOTE 2: After calling GameEngineCallback.houseResult(int, GameEngine)  
 this method should also call Player.resetBet() on each player in preparation for 
 the next round
        Parameters:
        delay - the delay between cards being dealt (in milliseconds (ms))
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - thrown when delay param is < 0
        See Also:
        dealPlayer(Player, int)

      • applyWinLoss

        void applyWinLoss​(Player player,
                  int houseResult)
         A player's bet is settled by this method 
 i.e. win or loss is applied to update betting points 
 based on a comparison of the player result and the provided houseResult
 
 NOTE: This method is usually called from dealHouse(int) 
 as described above but is included in the public interface to facilitate testing
        Parameters:
        player - - the Player to apply win/loss to
        houseResult - - a DicePair containing the house result

        Parameters:

      • addGameEngineCallback

        void addGameEngineCallback​(GameEngineCallback gameEngineCallback)
        Parameters:
        gameEngineCallback - 
         a client specific implementation of GameEngineCallback used to perform display updates etc.
 Callbacks should be called in the order they were added
 NOTE: you will use a different implementation of the GameEngineCallback 
       for the console (assignment 1) and GUI (assignment 2) versions
        See Also:
